366
00:21:40.182 --> 00:21:43.852
So as you heard from the previous presentation, clonal hematopoiesis

367
00:21:43.872 --> 00:21:47.652
or CHIP is an age-associated phenomenon in which hematopoietic

368
00:21:47.732 --> 00:21:51.332
stem and progenitor cells acquire mutations and expand in the

369
00:21:51.352 --> 00:21:55.201
blood. In non-small cell lung cancer, 30%

370
00:21:55.252 --> 00:21:57.692
of patients have CHIP.

371
00:21:58.512 --> 00:22:02.452
And out of these patients, in

372
00:22:02.552 --> 00:22:06.272
over 40%, these mutant cells can also infiltrate the lung

373
00:22:06.352 --> 00:22:09.872
tumors interacting with the cells in the lung tumor environment.

374
00:22:10.692 --> 00:22:14.372
And we have termed this tumor-infiltrating clonal hematopoiesis or

375
00:22:14.412 --> 00:22:15.492
TICH for short.

376
00:22:16.952 --> 00:22:20.342
And importantly, as also shown already in the previous presentation,

377
00:22:20.792 --> 00:22:24.782
patients with TICH, but not patients with blood-only CHIP, have

378
00:22:24.852 --> 00:22:28.292
worse recurrence-free survival compared to patients without clonal

379
00:22:28.302 --> 00:22:29.112
hematopoiesis.

380
00:22:30.892 --> 00:22:34.722
And these findings are based on the first 400 patients, part of the

381
00:22:34.972 --> 00:22:38.832
TRACERx study. And today, I want to talk about the different

382
00:22:38.892 --> 00:22:42.592
ways we're trying to understand the longitudinal dynamics of CHIP

383
00:22:42.672 --> 00:22:46.092
clones and how CHIP cells shape their surroundings in the

384
00:22:46.172 --> 00:22:47.752
completed TRACERx study.

385
00:22:49.292 --> 00:22:53.252
So quick word about TRACERx. So TRACERx is a multicenter prospective

386
00:22:53.312 --> 00:22:57.152
observational study that tracks early-stage non-small cell lung

387
00:22:57.192 --> 00:22:59.212
cancer tumor evolution over time.

388
00:23:00.552 --> 00:23:01.732
And as part of TRACERx,

389
00:23:02.612 --> 00:23:04.832
various patient material has been collected,

390
00:23:05.692 --> 00:23:09.432
including paired blood samples, tumor tissue, and plasma

391
00:23:09.492 --> 00:23:13.382
samples, all of which can be used to not only study

392
00:23:13.492 --> 00:23:16.152
tumor evolution, but also clonal hematopoiesis.

393
00:23:17.482 --> 00:23:21.292
And today, I want to focus on these three topics

394
00:23:21.352 --> 00:23:25.092
here, starting with the prevalence and survival data in the completed

395
00:23:25.112 --> 00:23:28.112
TRACERx study, followed by longitudinal

396
00:23:28.772 --> 00:23:32.372
dynamics of the CHIP clones, and then ending with some molecular

397
00:23:32.452 --> 00:23:36.432
data about the microenvironment and how the CHIP cells

398
00:23:36.752 --> 00:23:38.052
shape their surroundings.

399
00:23:40.072 --> 00:23:44.022
So in the completed TRACERx study, we have almost 800 patients with

400
00:23:44.022 --> 00:23:47.732
baseline blood whole exome sequencing data that we can use

401
00:23:48.152 --> 00:23:51.332
to identify these CHIP mutations.

402
00:23:51.372 --> 00:23:52.292
And in this cohort,

403
00:23:53.212 --> 00:23:57.202
33% of the patients carry these CHIP mutations, and out of

404
00:23:57.232 --> 00:23:59.412
these, 43% have TICH.

405
00:24:00.352 --> 00:24:03.752
And here on the right, you can see that the most commonly mutated genes

406
00:24:04.132 --> 00:24:08.092
involve DNMT3A, TET2, and ASXL1 in

407
00:24:08.152 --> 00:24:10.832
line with findings from others.

408
00:24:12.772 --> 00:24:16.732
And here in gray, you can then also see the proportion of these mutations

409
00:24:16.792 --> 00:24:18.292
that are only present in blood,

410
00:24:19.252 --> 00:24:23.132
and then in red, the proportion of mutations that can, in addition, be

411
00:24:23.172 --> 00:24:24.652
identified in the tumors.

412
00:24:26.552 --> 00:24:30.532
And generally, the variable frequency of the CHIP mutations is

413
00:24:30.632 --> 00:24:34.612
lower in the tumors, as seen here at the bottom of

414
00:24:34.652 --> 00:24:38.012
the graph, compared to the variable frequency in the blood.

415
00:24:38.472 --> 00:24:42.012
And this is consistent in all the assessed

416
00:24:42.052 --> 00:24:44.264
genes.We then used

417
00:24:45.304 --> 00:24:49.064
the ratio of this variable of frequency in the

418
00:24:51.644 --> 00:24:54.844
tumor and blood to calculate a relative

419
00:24:55.264 --> 00:24:58.804
tumor-infiltrating clone size. And what we observed

420
00:24:59.204 --> 00:25:02.784
was that tumor-infiltrating clones containing TET2

421
00:25:03.224 --> 00:25:06.924
and DNMT3A mutations tended to be bigger compared to

422
00:25:06.984 --> 00:25:10.894
clones carrying CHIP mutations that are not

423
00:25:11.004 --> 00:25:12.164
as commonly observed.

424
00:25:13.464 --> 00:25:16.924
So this shows us that CHIP clones can infiltrate tumors, but they can

425
00:25:16.964 --> 00:25:20.244
infiltrate tumors differently based on the affected gene.

426
00:25:21.854 --> 00:25:25.764
And in the completed TRACERx study, we were able to again observe that indeed

427
00:25:25.784 --> 00:25:29.644
patients with TISH, but not patients with blood-only CHIP, have worse

428
00:25:30.084 --> 00:25:33.444
disease-free survival compared to patients without clonal hematopoiesis.

429
00:25:34.314 --> 00:25:37.324
And now to assessing more detail

430
00:25:38.364 --> 00:25:41.504
what the survival differences are

431
00:25:42.164 --> 00:25:46.113
derived from, we wanted to look at the longitudinal dynamics of

432
00:25:46.144 --> 00:25:49.924
these CHIP mutations. And for that, we took advantage of

433
00:25:50.164 --> 00:25:53.564
the ctDNA framework that we have set up for the TRACERx study,

434
00:25:54.164 --> 00:25:57.844
in which we have paired whole exome sequencing data from blood

435
00:25:58.144 --> 00:26:02.084
and tumors that we then use to create patient-specific mutation panels.

436
00:26:02.124 --> 00:26:05.844
And for a subset of patients, we then included also CHIP mutations in these

437
00:26:05.944 --> 00:26:06.304
panels.

438
00:26:07.704 --> 00:26:11.504
We then collected plasma samples longitudinally, allowing us to track

439
00:26:12.224 --> 00:26:14.064
the CHIP mutations from the cell-free DNA.

440
00:26:15.344 --> 00:26:16.844
And we have 37

441
00:26:18.064 --> 00:26:21.844
patients in which we can now longitudinally assess the

442
00:26:21.904 --> 00:26:23.264
evolution of these CHIP clones.

443
00:26:25.024 --> 00:26:28.824
So using now the cell-free DNA data in these 37 patients, we were

444
00:26:28.904 --> 00:26:32.424
specifically interested in understanding whether CHIP clones were

445
00:26:32.444 --> 00:26:36.344
expanding or contracting independent of whether the tumor is

446
00:26:36.384 --> 00:26:37.564
growing or shrinking.

447
00:26:38.664 --> 00:26:42.584
So when we first looked at the overall trajectory of the change in

448
00:26:42.624 --> 00:26:46.224
the variable of frequency over time of these CHIP mutations,

449
00:26:46.704 --> 00:26:50.634
we could see that indeed the CHIP clones are expanding over the course of the

450
00:26:50.684 --> 00:26:51.064
disease.

451
00:26:52.224 --> 00:26:56.044
When we then split the cohort into patients who

452
00:26:56.064 --> 00:26:59.704
received adjuvant treatment and patients who did not receive adjuvant treatment,

453
00:27:00.164 --> 00:27:03.944
we could see that the CHIP clones were actually expanding

454
00:27:04.004 --> 00:27:07.184
specifically in the patients who did not receive adjuvant

455
00:27:07.244 --> 00:27:10.944
treatment. We then went back to the survival

456
00:27:11.024 --> 00:27:14.684
data of the completed study. And as you can see

457
00:27:14.744 --> 00:27:18.704
here on the left, when we split the patients again into those

458
00:27:18.724 --> 00:27:22.444
who received or did not receive adjuvant treatment, that the

459
00:27:22.484 --> 00:27:26.004
effect of TISH on survival was particularly prominent in an adjuvant

460
00:27:26.084 --> 00:27:27.944
treatment-naive setting.

461
00:27:30.944 --> 00:27:34.804
To better understand how CHIP cells now shape their surroundings,

462
00:27:35.304 --> 00:27:38.604
we created a detailed overview of

463
00:27:38.664 --> 00:27:40.544
the immune landscape of

464
00:27:41.944 --> 00:27:42.924
the microenvironments

465
00:27:43.784 --> 00:27:47.324
in patients with CHIP and without CHIP using two different

466
00:27:47.844 --> 00:27:49.184
single-cell multi-omics approaches.

467
00:27:49.884 --> 00:27:53.844
First, we used TargetSeq for simultaneous single-cell genotyping

468
00:27:54.244 --> 00:27:57.984
and gene expression analysis to specifically look at differences in

469
00:27:58.024 --> 00:28:01.764
TET2 mutant and TET2 wild type cells within the same patient.

470
00:28:02.764 --> 00:28:06.393
And then to look at more global gene regulation differences between

471
00:28:06.484 --> 00:28:09.884
patients that had TISH to patients that did not have clonal

472
00:28:09.904 --> 00:28:13.444
hematopoiesis, we used DogmaSeq for simultaneous

473
00:28:13.864 --> 00:28:17.854
chromatin accessibility, gene expression, and immunophenotype analysis.

474
00:28:19.404 --> 00:28:23.144
And using the TargetSeq data, we could see that TET2 mutant cells were

475
00:28:23.164 --> 00:28:26.664
enriched in myeloid cells, meaning monocytes, macrophages, and dendritic cells,

476
00:28:27.064 --> 00:28:29.604
in line with what others have also seen.

477
00:28:30.314 --> 00:28:33.944
And interestingly, we also observed an enrichment of TET2 mutant cells

478
00:28:34.664 --> 00:28:37.964
in NK cells. And in contrast, T and B cells

479
00:28:38.224 --> 00:28:40.824
consisted largely of TET2 wild type cells.

480
00:28:42.304 --> 00:28:45.964
And while these TET2 mutant cells showed clear lineage skewing,

481
00:28:46.354 --> 00:28:49.444
they did not seem to show prominent transcriptomic differences.

482
00:28:50.304 --> 00:28:53.944
And this, in part, can already be seen in the UMAP on the left,

483
00:28:54.384 --> 00:28:57.924
where you can see this intermixing of mutant and wild type TET2

484
00:28:58.004 --> 00:29:01.394
cells with one another. So this led us to

485
00:29:01.464 --> 00:29:05.204
hypothesize that maybe the microenvironment in

486
00:29:05.243 --> 00:29:09.224
which the CHIP cells are residing is generally already altered

487
00:29:09.284 --> 00:29:11.924
and is not restricted to only the

488
00:29:13.864 --> 00:29:14.544
mutant cells.

489
00:29:16.064 --> 00:29:19.824
To assess this hypothesis, we then went or turned into our second

490
00:29:19.884 --> 00:29:23.404
single-cell cohort, and now comparing patients that had

491
00:29:23.444 --> 00:29:26.484
TISH to patients that did not have clonal hematopoiesis.

492
00:29:27.404 --> 00:29:29.724
And today, I will focus on some of the

493
00:29:31.824 --> 00:29:35.704
transcriptomic findings of the immune subset of the cohort.

494
00:29:37.984 --> 00:29:41.564
When we first looked at cell type abundance differences

495
00:29:42.324 --> 00:29:46.124
in the immune subset, we could see an upregulation of gamma delta T

496
00:29:46.204 --> 00:29:50.124
cells and cycling T cells, specifically in the patients that had

497
00:29:50.144 --> 00:29:53.444
TISH compared to patients that did not have clonal hematopoiesis.

498
00:29:53.824 --> 00:29:57.564
And this on the right, you can see that the gamma delta T cells were

499
00:29:57.604 --> 00:30:01.544
particularly rich in the tumor tissue compared

500
00:30:01.564 --> 00:30:05.464
to BPMCs, tumor adjacent normal tissue in the same

501
00:30:05.544 --> 00:30:05.944
patient.

502
00:30:07.604 --> 00:30:11.304
When we looked at more global changes, we observed an

503
00:30:11.344 --> 00:30:15.324
upregulation of genes involved in the interferon response in the

504
00:30:15.364 --> 00:30:18.944
patient that had TISH compared to patients that did not have clonal

505
00:30:18.964 --> 00:30:22.624
hematopoiesis, in line with increased abundance of gamma delta T

506
00:30:22.704 --> 00:30:22.964
cells.

507
00:30:24.464 --> 00:30:28.224
So this suggests that the microenvironment with CHIP cells undergoes

508
00:30:28.264 --> 00:30:31.784
immune remodeling, which is likely driven by the

509
00:30:31.824 --> 00:30:33.464
presence of these CHIP cells.

510
00:30:35.804 --> 00:30:39.664
So to summarize, I've shown you today that TISH drives worse

511
00:30:39.744 --> 00:30:43.464
outcomes in non-small cell lung cancer, particularly in a

512
00:30:43.504 --> 00:30:47.488
non-adjuvant setting.I've also shown you that CHIP mutations expand

513
00:30:47.528 --> 00:30:51.227
over time in these patients who did not receive adjuvant systemic

