00:35:37.008 --> 00:35:38.648
Good afternoon. I'm Shuang Li.

601
00:35:39.468 --> 00:35:43.448
Thank you for the introduction, and it's my

602
00:35:43.458 --> 00:35:47.208
honor to present our study about the TFF2

603
00:35:47.218 --> 00:35:51.088
deficiency amplifies IL-1 beta-driven inflammation

604
00:35:51.128 --> 00:35:54.508
and promotes aging-associated gastric tumor progression.

605
00:35:57.148 --> 00:36:00.988
This study is supported by Tonix Pharmaceuticals, and several

606
00:36:01.068 --> 00:36:04.348
co-authors are affiliated with the company.

607
00:36:06.528 --> 00:36:10.408
As we know, aging is a major risk factor for gastric cancer,

608
00:36:10.868 --> 00:36:14.208
but the underlying mechanism remain poorly defined.

609
00:36:14.828 --> 00:36:18.608
One of the key feature of aging is the chronic low-grade

610
00:36:18.728 --> 00:36:21.948
inflammation, which is known as inflammaging.

611
00:36:22.648 --> 00:36:26.608
During the inflammaging, the immune system undergoes

612
00:36:26.628 --> 00:36:30.528
a significant remodeling, including the myeloid

613
00:36:30.568 --> 00:36:33.888
scarring in bone marrow, expansion of

614
00:36:33.988 --> 00:36:37.708
MDSCs, and increased pro-inflammatory

615
00:36:37.788 --> 00:36:38.628
cytokines.

616
00:36:41.128 --> 00:36:44.228
TFF2 is a member of the trefoil factor family,

617
00:36:44.708 --> 00:36:48.578
primarily expressed in gastric mucous neck cells, and

618
00:36:48.728 --> 00:36:52.108
plays key roles in epithelial protection and immune

619
00:36:52.148 --> 00:36:52.808
regulation.

620
00:36:53.712 --> 00:36:57.692
In our previous work, we fused TIF2 with murine serum

621
00:36:57.752 --> 00:37:00.092
albumin to develop a peptide

622
00:37:00.172 --> 00:37:03.592
TIF2-MSA with enhanced stability.

623
00:37:04.492 --> 00:37:07.972
TIF2-MSA can function as a partial agonist of

624
00:37:08.132 --> 00:37:11.452
CXCR4 and synergizes with PD1

625
00:37:11.532 --> 00:37:15.172
blockade to suppress gastric tumor progression.

626
00:37:16.072 --> 00:37:19.822
However, whether TIF2 regulates age-associated

627
00:37:19.972 --> 00:37:23.412
inflammation and the tumor progression remains unknown.

628
00:37:25.712 --> 00:37:28.292
So here are the key findings from our study.

629
00:37:28.872 --> 00:37:32.652
First, we identify that TIF2-positive epithelial

630
00:37:32.692 --> 00:37:35.172
cells are reduced in the aged stomach.

631
00:37:37.352 --> 00:37:41.212
We compare young mice at three months old and

632
00:37:41.372 --> 00:37:43.812
aged mice at 18 months old.

633
00:37:45.252 --> 00:37:49.172
In our previous study, TIF2 marks both the

634
00:37:49.212 --> 00:37:52.172
mucus neck cell and the progenitor population.

635
00:37:52.932 --> 00:37:56.512
So on the left, we found that the TIF2-positive cell

636
00:37:57.212 --> 00:38:01.122
decline in the aged stomach, both in the corpus and

637
00:38:01.272 --> 00:38:02.132
in the antrum.

638
00:38:02.972 --> 00:38:06.552
And on the right, we found that in the single-cell

639
00:38:06.672 --> 00:38:10.622
RNA seq data, the progenitor score is decreased in

640
00:38:10.652 --> 00:38:11.712
the aged stomach.

641
00:38:13.192 --> 00:38:16.832
And we also find that the TIF2 probe

642
00:38:16.912 --> 00:38:20.612
labeled progenitor cells are decreased in the aged stomach.

643
00:38:23.892 --> 00:38:27.472
Based on the loss of TIF2-positive cells, we

644
00:38:27.532 --> 00:38:31.512
wanted to know whether the TIF2 reduction is

645
00:38:31.572 --> 00:38:32.812
global in the aged

646
00:38:34.712 --> 00:38:38.472
mice. So we find that in the single

647
00:38:38.592 --> 00:38:42.472
RNA cell data, the TIF2 expression is reduced in

648
00:38:42.532 --> 00:38:46.312
the aged stomach. And the TIF2 protein is also

649
00:38:46.352 --> 00:38:49.872
declined in both the stomach and in the serum.

650
00:38:51.792 --> 00:38:55.492
However, this change seems to be a stomach

651
00:38:55.732 --> 00:38:59.612
specific change, as we do not see a similar change

652
00:38:59.672 --> 00:39:01.612
in the duodenum or the pancreas.

653
00:39:04.392 --> 00:39:08.212
Next, we want to know how the aging changes the

654
00:39:08.292 --> 00:39:09.612
immune microenvironment.

655
00:39:10.992 --> 00:39:14.812
We found that the PMN MDSCs accumulate in

656
00:39:14.872 --> 00:39:17.072
both the stomach and in the blood.

657
00:39:17.952 --> 00:39:21.832
And there is a myeloid bias in the bone marrow, as

658
00:39:22.632 --> 00:39:25.452
reflected by the GMP population

659
00:39:26.152 --> 00:39:27.092
upregulation.

660
00:39:27.972 --> 00:39:31.872
And we also see in the elevated inflammatory cytokines such

661
00:39:31.952 --> 00:39:34.512
as IL6 and the TNF alpha

662
00:39:35.472 --> 00:39:36.382
in the stomach,

663
00:39:37.432 --> 00:39:40.332
which shows gastric and systemic

664
00:39:40.412 --> 00:39:42.512
inflammaging during the aging.

665
00:39:44.912 --> 00:39:48.472
To investigate the causal link between TIF2 loss

666
00:39:48.852 --> 00:39:52.512
and the MDSC expansion, we use the

667
00:39:52.652 --> 00:39:55.532
TIF2 heterozygous and knockout mice.

668
00:39:56.132 --> 00:39:56.812
We found that

669
00:39:58.052 --> 00:40:01.592
PMN MDSCs accumulate in both the stomach

670
00:40:01.952 --> 00:40:02.912
and in the blood.

671
00:40:03.752 --> 00:40:07.281
Also, we see that the CD8 positive T cells are reduced,

672
00:40:07.852 --> 00:40:11.672
indicating a immunosuppressive phenotype, mirrors

673
00:40:11.772 --> 00:40:13.372
what we see in the aged mice.

674
00:40:16.192 --> 00:40:20.172
Next, we want to know whether restoring TIF2 can reverse

675
00:40:20.182 --> 00:40:23.672
this MDSC expansion and inflammaging.

676
00:40:24.552 --> 00:40:28.532
We use TIF2-MSA in this experiment, and we found that

677
00:40:28.692 --> 00:40:32.192
the TIF2-MSA can reduce PMN MDSC

678
00:40:32.252 --> 00:40:36.092
accumulation and partially restore circulating CD8

679
00:40:36.172 --> 00:40:36.752
T cells.

680
00:40:37.612 --> 00:40:41.332
And it can also reverse myeloid bias in the bone marrow,

681
00:40:41.872 --> 00:40:45.112
as reflected by the MPP3 and the GMP

682
00:40:45.492 --> 00:40:47.572
upregulation in the bone marrow.

683
00:40:48.552 --> 00:40:52.112
And this suggests that restoring TIF2 can

684
00:40:52.172 --> 00:40:55.572
reverse the PMN MDSC expansion and the systemic

685
00:40:55.712 --> 00:40:56.422
inflammaging.

686
00:40:59.372 --> 00:41:02.772
So next, we want to know how the aging affects the tumor

687
00:41:02.812 --> 00:41:06.672
progression. To address this, we use two complementary

688
00:41:06.952 --> 00:41:10.911
gastric tumor models. One is the ACKP syngenic

689
00:41:11.012 --> 00:41:14.442
orthotopic model, and one is the MNU-induced

690
00:41:14.572 --> 00:41:15.692
gastric cancer model.

691
00:41:16.632 --> 00:41:20.532
We found that in the ACKP model, aging enhances the

692
00:41:20.632 --> 00:41:24.432
tumor growth and the tumor burden, and also causes a shorter

693
00:41:24.592 --> 00:41:25.582
overall survival.

694
00:41:26.662 --> 00:41:30.192
And in the MNU model, we see a consistent

695
00:41:30.872 --> 00:41:31.252
data.

696
00:41:34.052 --> 00:41:36.712
And then we investigate the tumor

697
00:41:36.752 --> 00:41:40.632
microenvironment. We found that in

698
00:41:40.652 --> 00:41:44.512
the aged tumor microenvironment, PMN MDSCs are

699
00:41:44.632 --> 00:41:48.552
expanded and exhibit elevated IL1

700
00:41:48.612 --> 00:41:52.012
beta expression. PDGF alpha

701
00:41:52.332 --> 00:41:55.692
positive, IL1R1 positive CAFs are also

702
00:41:55.752 --> 00:41:58.312
elevated in the aged gastric tumors.

703
00:41:58.852 --> 00:42:02.792
This suggests that the PMN MDSCs derived IL1

704
00:42:02.852 --> 00:42:06.772
beta interacted with the IL1R1 positive CAFs in the tumor

705
00:42:06.852 --> 00:42:09.572
microenvironment and contributes to

706
00:42:09.832 --> 00:42:13.332
immunosuppressive and the tumor promoting niche.

707
00:42:16.292 --> 00:42:20.112
And in order to know whether restoring TIF2 could limit

708
00:42:20.132 --> 00:42:23.412
this age-associated tumor progression, we use

709
00:42:23.492 --> 00:42:25.732
TIF2-MSA as a pretreatment.

710
00:42:26.792 --> 00:42:30.712
We found that pretreatment with TIF2-MSA can reduce

711
00:42:30.772 --> 00:42:33.572
the tumor growth and burden in the aged mice.

712
00:42:34.312 --> 00:42:37.832
And the effect of TIF2-MSA is consistent across

713
00:42:37.892 --> 00:42:40.892
ACKP orthotopic model and the

714
00:42:41.052 --> 00:42:42.872
MNU-induced models.

715
00:42:43.812 --> 00:42:47.352
And this supports that the TIF2-MSA could

716
00:42:47.432 --> 00:42:50.652
limit the age-associated tumor progression.

717
00:42:53.332 --> 00:42:56.692
And then we look at the tumor microenvironment.

718
00:42:57.432 --> 00:43:01.072
We found that the TIF2-MSA could reduce the PMN

719
00:43:01.292 --> 00:43:03.612
MDSCs and the PDGF

720
00:43:03.672 --> 00:43:07.508
alphaPositive IL1RN, positive CAFs

721
00:43:07.568 --> 00:43:11.368
in the aged tumors, and the CD8 T cells

722
00:43:11.428 --> 00:43:14.968
are increased following TIF2 restoration.

723
00:43:15.148 --> 00:43:19.028
This suggests that the TIF2 MSA could reverse the

724
00:43:19.068 --> 00:43:21.668
immunosuppressive tumor microenvironment.

725
00:43:25.168 --> 00:43:28.828
In summary, we propose that aging-associated

726
00:43:28.928 --> 00:43:32.288
loss of TIF2 drives systemic inflammaging,

727
00:43:33.128 --> 00:43:36.808
including MDSC expansion in stomach and in

728
00:43:36.828 --> 00:43:40.308
circulation, myeloid base in the bone marrow,

729
00:43:40.528 --> 00:43:44.328
and inflammatory cytokines elevation in the circulation.

730
00:43:45.228 --> 00:43:48.188
The MDSC-derived IL1B activates

731
00:43:48.628 --> 00:43:51.988
IL1RN positive CAFs and establish a

732
00:43:52.028 --> 00:43:54.008
tumor-promoting microenvironment.

733
00:43:54.888 --> 00:43:58.268
Restoring TIF2 signaling limits this cascade

734
00:43:58.368 --> 00:44:00.968
and attenuates tumor progression.

735
