1288
01:16:43.364 --> 01:16:47.184
Good afternoon, everyone. I'm Manon Penco-Campillo, a postdoctoral fellow

1289
01:16:47.204 --> 01:16:50.984
in Dr. Wainwright laboratory in Loyola University of Chicago.

1290
01:16:51.064 --> 01:16:55.004
And today I present my work on how age-dependent neuroimmune changes

1291
01:16:55.064 --> 01:16:58.864
in glioblastoma shape therapeutic response and reveal senescent

1292
01:16:58.944 --> 01:17:01.584
microglia as a targetable vulnerability.

1293
01:17:02.804 --> 01:17:03.704
I have no disclosure.

1294
01:17:05.024 --> 01:17:07.903
So first, a short introduction on glioblastoma.

1295
01:17:07.984 --> 01:17:11.684
Glioblastoma is the most common aggressive malignant brain tumor in adults,

1296
01:17:12.124 --> 01:17:15.584
representing 50% to 60% of central nervous system tumor,

1297
01:17:16.384 --> 01:17:20.144
with 22,000 new cases and approximately 50,000

1298
01:17:20.224 --> 01:17:22.264
deaths per year in the United States.

1299
01:17:23.144 --> 01:17:27.004
The median age at the diagnosis is comprising between

1300
01:17:27.264 --> 01:17:28.804
68 and 70 years old.

1301
01:17:29.764 --> 01:17:33.404
The standard of care has not changed since 2005 and

1302
01:17:33.464 --> 01:17:36.804
relies on maximum resection, radiotherapy,

1303
01:17:37.184 --> 01:17:40.844
concurrent temozolomide, followed by adjuvant temozolomide.

1304
01:17:40.933 --> 01:17:44.724
Despite this aggressive treatment, outcomes remain poor, with a median

1305
01:17:44.804 --> 01:17:47.984
overall survival about 14.6 months.

1306
01:17:48.844 --> 01:17:52.454
And all clinical trial with immunotherapy have

1307
01:17:52.484 --> 01:17:56.394
failed. So overall, glioblastoma remains one of the most

1308
01:17:56.424 --> 01:18:00.264
challenging cancer to treat, with minimal therapeutic progress over

1309
01:18:00.284 --> 01:18:01.304
the two last decades.

1310
01:18:02.804 --> 01:18:06.544
Here, we first showed and confirmed the poor overall survival

1311
01:18:06.604 --> 01:18:10.024
in older glioblastoma patients. For that, SEER

1312
01:18:10.064 --> 01:18:13.864
database was analyzed across all age group for overall

1313
01:18:13.924 --> 01:18:17.444
survival. And as you can see, patient in the range

1314
01:18:17.664 --> 01:18:21.464
18, 44 years old present a median overall survival of

1315
01:18:21.484 --> 01:18:25.264
1.58 years, and this survival decreases

1316
01:18:25.344 --> 01:18:29.264
with progressive aging until it reaches 0.25 years

1317
01:18:29.304 --> 01:18:32.884
for patient over 75 years old. So this

1318
01:18:32.944 --> 01:18:36.904
data indicate that increased age is a negative prognostic factor

1319
01:18:36.944 --> 01:18:38.203
for glioblastoma patient.

1320
01:18:39.844 --> 01:18:43.624
Then we wanted to know where this negative aging effect comes from.

1321
01:18:44.344 --> 01:18:46.004
In this study, the author

1322
01:18:46.944 --> 01:18:50.764
look at the tumor for being associated with age or

1323
01:18:50.804 --> 01:18:54.464
not. So they took the tumor from patient, and they looked on

1324
01:18:54.544 --> 01:18:56.384
cancers including glioblastoma.

1325
01:18:57.084 --> 01:19:01.064
And for glioblastoma, the RNA sequencing does not reveal any

1326
01:19:01.524 --> 01:19:05.264
significant changing in term of gene expression when comparing younger

1327
01:19:05.304 --> 01:19:07.144
versus older glioblastoma patient.

1328
01:19:07.764 --> 01:19:11.004
So that tumor doesn't reflect their chronological age.

1329
01:19:11.564 --> 01:19:15.064
And we confirm this data with a single-cell RNA sequencing.

1330
01:19:15.824 --> 01:19:19.664
So based on this data, we hypothesized that the

1331
01:19:19.724 --> 01:19:23.324
major age-dependent changing in term of survival

1332
01:19:23.824 --> 01:19:27.544
does not come from inside of the tumor but comes from outside of the tumor

1333
01:19:27.584 --> 01:19:31.392
mass.To test this hypothesis, we

1334
01:19:31.472 --> 01:19:35.312
used the MRI guided biopsies to identify different

1335
01:19:35.352 --> 01:19:37.552
tumor region, different brain region.

1336
01:19:38.052 --> 01:19:41.892
So as you can see here, we identified the tumor core versus the

1337
01:19:41.952 --> 01:19:45.232
peritumoral region, which is right around the tumor.

1338
01:19:46.292 --> 01:19:49.762
And as we can see, the glioblastoma patient tumor core and

1339
01:19:49.852 --> 01:19:53.412
peritumoral brain have a distinct cellular composition.

1340
01:19:53.892 --> 01:19:57.512
For example, the peritumoral show more oligodendrocyte and

1341
01:19:57.672 --> 01:20:01.612
microglia as compared to the tumor core that present more malignant

1342
01:20:01.672 --> 01:20:02.071
cells.

1343
01:20:04.192 --> 01:20:08.152
Then we decided to focus on senescence because we know that senescence

1344
01:20:08.272 --> 01:20:11.812
increase with progressive aging and might play a role in

1345
01:20:12.432 --> 01:20:15.952
the different survival between younger versus older glioblastoma

1346
01:20:16.072 --> 01:20:16.452
patient.

1347
01:20:17.392 --> 01:20:20.792
So here we showed the mean senescence score, which is an

1348
01:20:20.852 --> 01:20:24.412
accumulation of different senescence gene signatures.

1349
01:20:24.532 --> 01:20:28.112
And we compared two different group of age for

1350
01:20:28.132 --> 01:20:31.672
glioblastoma patient, younger than 64 years old versus

1351
01:20:32.132 --> 01:20:35.972
older than 65 years old. For those two different region that we

1352
01:20:36.032 --> 01:20:39.462
saw right before, the peritumoral region and the tumor core.

1353
01:20:40.332 --> 01:20:43.412
So we saw that for glioblastoma patient,

1354
01:20:43.672 --> 01:20:47.652
the peritumoral tissue is enriched for

1355
01:20:47.732 --> 01:20:51.372
senescent cells with a P value of 0.1,

1356
01:20:51.752 --> 01:20:54.712
and especially in the microglia cell type.

1357
01:20:56.792 --> 01:21:00.652
So to confirm this increase of senescence that

1358
01:21:00.712 --> 01:21:04.552
we saw in human patient in mice, we used two months

1359
01:21:04.692 --> 01:21:08.092
old for young versus 24 months old for old

1360
01:21:08.532 --> 01:21:12.392
C57 black 6 mice that are intracranially injected

1361
01:21:12.472 --> 01:21:16.312
with glioblastoma cells SB28. To quantify the

1362
01:21:16.372 --> 01:21:19.952
senescence, I perform flow cytometric quantification of cells that are

1363
01:21:19.972 --> 01:21:23.472
positive for the beta-galactosidase, the marker of senescence.

1364
01:21:24.012 --> 01:21:27.752
And I compare those two different region, which is the extraterminal brain

1365
01:21:27.792 --> 01:21:29.332
